===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[Image:Wedge-1.jpg|150px|right]]

# One of the [[simple machine]]s; A piece of material, such as metal or wood, thick at one edge and tapered to a thin edge at the other for insertion in a narrow crevice, used for splitting, tightening, securing, or levering ([[w:Wedge (mechanical device)|Wikipedia article]]).
# {{context|colloquial|UK}} A quantity of money.
#: ''I made a big fat '''wedge''' from that job.''
# {{archaic}} A flank of cavalry acting to split some portion of an opposing army, charging in an inverted V formation.
# A group of [[goose|geese]] or [[swan]]s when they are in flight in a V formation.

